This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the detection of biomarkers in OCT images. The use of Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) and Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of ophthalmic pharmaceutical products suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for prediction indicates that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
